    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2007-03-29", 
    "text": "Charitable Driving Tax Relief Act of 2007 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to provide that volunteers who use their automobiles for the benefit of a charitable organization may exclude from their gross income reimbursements for their automobile operating expenses at the same level as business employees (i.e., 48.5 cents per mile in 2007)."
